<chapter xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude"  xml:id="chap_bases_dimension">
  <title>Bases and Dimension</title>
  <introduction>
    <objectives>
      <ul>
        <li>
          <p>
            What is the dimension of a subspace of <m>\R^n</m>?
            What property of bases makes the dimension a well-defined number?
          </p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <p>
            If <m>W</m> is a subspace of <m>\R^n</m> with dimension <m>k</m>,
            what must be true about any linearly independent subset <m>S</m> of <m>W</m> that contains exactly <m>k</m> vectors?
          </p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <p>
            If <m>W</m> is a subspace of <m>\R^n</m> with dimension <m>k</m>,
            what must be true about any subset <m>S</m> of <m>W</m> that contains exactly <m>k</m> vectors and spans <m>W</m>?
          </p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <p>
            What is the rank of a matrix?
          </p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <p>
            What does the Rank-Nullity Theorem say?
          </p>
        </li>
      </ul>
    </objectives>
  </introduction>
